Package software.leonov.common.base

Class BinaryFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • software.leonov.common.base.BinaryFunctions
  • public final class BinaryFunctions
extends Object
    Static utility methods pertaining to BinaryFunction instances.

    The methods in this class return serializable BinaryFunctions as long as they are given serializable parameters.

    Note: The BinaryFunction interface is the legacy version of BiFunction. It has been refactored to extend BiFunction for backwards compatibility. Java 8+ users should reference BiFunction directly.

    For example: BiFunction<Object, Object, T> bf = BinaryFunctions.constant(value);

    Author:
    Zhenya Leonov
